I've just been thinking a lot about this recently and thought I should share. It's not exactly anything new, but I thought I could shed my philosophy on the subject

Talking, Not talking, Acting, And not acting are what make this world go around. It's just up to us how we decide to express those feelings. If they're gonna be uplifting or degrading or if they're gonna be constructive and supportive or demeaning and rude.

This also works for your lack of words too. We were given the gift of communication to express our feelings and not keep them bottled up inside. And by keeping things to yourself or not talking you can also drastically effect the way things change.

I know this might not make the most amount of sense, but what you say and do will change the way that people act around you. This is literally the act of making the world you want to live in, you just gotta know the right words to say, and the right actions to do.
You could say something to someone only for that person to share it with another person and then they are talking with you about the thing they like because you introduced it to that first someone.

And it can happen without you even knowing it. You could say something that you thought to be a throwaway line only for the person you said that to to be completely enraptured by that subject and take it to heart 10 years down the road.

I've been thinking about this a lot recently and I think it's something that everyone should take to heart, even though it's super obvious:

Your words have so much power. What you say and do, can drastically effect the lives and events of so many others
